The paper discusses a new class of algorithms for reinforcement learning, specifically Q-learning, with a focus on sample complexity bounds. This topic falls under the subfield of machine learning, particularly in the areas of reinforcement learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
